<div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-20);">
  <div class="container--prose">

    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-6); border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-ink);">
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-masthead); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3.815rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Resources</h1>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ink-muted); line-height: var(--leading-loose); max-width: 60ch;">
        Organizations, communities, and websites for freethought, secular humanism, and rational inquiry.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">

      <h2>Organizations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://ffrf.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Freedom From Religion Foundation</a></strong> &mdash; The largest freethought organization in North America. Advocates for separation of church and state.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.secularhumanism.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Council for Secular Humanism</a></strong> &mdash; Educational programs and publications promoting secular humanist principles.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://americanhumanist.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">American Humanist Association</a></strong> &mdash; The oldest humanist organization in the US, founded 1941.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.atheists.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">American Atheists</a></strong> &mdash; Civil rights advocacy for atheists. Founded by Madalyn Murray O'Hair in 1963.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://centerforinquiry.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Center for Inquiry</a></strong> &mdash; Promotes science, reason, and secular values through research and education.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.secular.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Secular Coalition for America</a></strong> &mdash; Lobbying and advocacy for secular government policy.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.humanistsinternational.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Humanists International</a></strong> &mdash; Global umbrella for humanist, rationalist, and secularist organizations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Publications & Media</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://secularhumanism.org/free-inquiry/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Free Inquiry</a></strong> &mdash; Bimonthly magazine of the Council for Secular Humanism.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://skepticalinquirer.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skeptical Inquirer</a></strong> &mdash; The magazine for science and reason. Published by the Committee for Skeptical Inquiry.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://thehumanist.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Humanist</a></strong> &mdash; Magazine of the American Humanist Association, published since 1941.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://newhumanist.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">New Humanist</a></strong> &mdash; UK-based magazine on ideas, culture, and society from a humanist perspective.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Online Communities</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/atheism/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">r/atheism</a></strong> &mdash; Reddit community with over 2 million members.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/freethought/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">r/freethought</a></strong> &mdash; Reddit community for freethought discussion.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/humanism/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">r/humanism</a></strong> &mdash; Reddit community for secular humanist discussion.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/topics/atheism/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Atheist Meetups</a></strong> &mdash; Local meetup groups for secular community.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Texts & Archives</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.gutenberg.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Project Gutenberg</a></strong> &mdash; Free access to thousands of public domain texts including Ingersoll, Paine, Russell, and Hume.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://infidels.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Internet Infidels</a></strong> &mdash; Secular web with an extensive library of essays, debates, and references on atheism and freethought.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://freethought-trail.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Freethought Trail</a></strong> &mdash; Historical sites of the American freethought movement, with biographies and maps.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.sacred-texts.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sacred Texts Archive</a></strong> &mdash; Comprehensive archive of religious texts from all traditions, useful for comparative study.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Podcasts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://ffrf.org/news/radio" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Freethought Radio</a></strong> &mdash; Weekly podcast from the Freedom From Religion Foundation.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.skepticality.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skepticality</a></strong> &mdash; One of the longest-running skeptical podcasts.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.pointofinquiry.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Point of Inquiry</a></strong> &mdash; The Center for Inquiry's flagship podcast on science, secularism, and society.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>For Young People</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.campquest.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Camp Quest</a></strong> &mdash; Summer camps for children of secular families.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.secularstudents.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Secular Student Alliance</a></strong> &mdash; Support and resources for secular student groups on campuses.</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-10); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink-faint);">
        Know a resource that should be listed here? <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">Let us know</a>.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
